extends ../layouts/index

block content
  main.main
    div.intro.intro--badge.intro--background(style=backgroundImageStyle('images/photos/2015-10-22_11-17-44.jpg'))
      div.intro__container
        div.intro__primary
          h1.intro__heading Holiday Club
          p.intro__body Our action-packed Holiday Club is located at Sefton Park School, keeping children from Bristol entertained with a variety of activities and exciting day trips. We offer full or half-day care for children aged 3-7 in the Terrapin and for children aged 8-14 years in Hut 6338, helping busy families during half-term and the summer break.
        div.intro__secondary
          div.intro__badge
            div.intro__badge-wrap
              img.intro__badge-image(src=assetUrl('images/cooking.png'))

    div.main__container
      div.content
        section
          img.content__image.content__image--float(src=assetUrl('images/photos/2017-03-08_21-41-00.jpg'))
          p Each week, Holiday Club and Taningua club have a different theme so new experiences can be had – such as Bollywood, Vintage Sports, Circus Skills, and Japanese Pop Culture. For more information about what we’ll be up to this summer, please download our #[a(href=assetUrl('files/holiday-club-summer-2017-programme.pdf')) Summer Holiday Club Programme].
          p Booking for the Summer Holiday Club and Taningua will open on the 13th of June. Get your booking in between the 13th of June and the 7th of July to benefit from our early bird 10% discount!

        section
          h2 Our ethos
          p At Sparks, we believe the school holidays should be about meeting new people, learning new skills, being active and, most importantly,  having bundles of fun!
          p We offer a safe environment where your children can play freely inside and out, with a variety of optional planned activities to choose from each day.

        section
          h2 Where, when and who
          p Holiday Club takes place during half term, Easter and summer school holidays, and is held at #[a(href=map.seftonPark) Sefton Park School, St Bartholomew’s Road, Bristol, BS7 9BJ].
          p We welcome children from East and Central Bristol, and provide a great environment for making new friends.

        section
          h2 Things to do
          ul
            li Arts & crafts
            li Cooking
            li Den building
            li Dressing up
            li Sewing
            li Outdoor play: skateboarding, rollerblading, scootering, tennis, football, water play
            li Toys & boardgames
            li Trips to places near and far
            li Computers (max 20 mins per day)
            li Television (a choice of films to end the day)
          p Children aged 8-14 can enjoy our #[a(href=pageUrl('clubs/taningua.pug')) Taningua Club] with activities catered to more mature interests, such as photography, archery, cookery and paintball.
          a.content__download(href=assetUrl('files/holiday-club-summer-2017-programme.pdf')) Download the Summer Holiday Club 2017 Programme

        section
          h2 What to bring
          img.content__image.content__image--float(src=assetUrl('images/photos/2017-03-08_21-40-00.jpg'))
          p Essential items to bring along…
          ul
            li Packed lunch with a drink
            li Weather appropriate clothing (coats, hats, gloves)
            li Change of clothing and wellies
            li Swimming costume and towel
            li Spending money (optional)
            li Medication*
          p
            em *We must have written permission from a parent or guardian to supply medication.

        section
          h2 Dates
          p We publish the schedules as early as possible so you can view each day’s activities and find out what the theme will be before choosing which days to book for your child.
          p Our Holiday Club dates for 2017 are as follows:
          ol
            li February – Feb 13th to Feb 17th
            li Easter – Apr 10th to Apr 21st #[em (excl. Apr 14th and 17th bank holidays)]
            li May – not operating
            li Summer – Jul 24th to Sep 1st
            li October – Oct 23rd to Oct 27th

        section
          h2 Sessions & prices
          table
            thead
              tr
                th Session
                th Price per child
            tbody
              tr
                td 08:15 – 17:45
                td £31.00
              tr
                td 08:15 - 13:00
                td £15.50
              tr
                td 13:00 - 17:45
                td £15.50
              tr
                td 09:00 - 15:30
                td £22.00
          p
            strong N.B. There is a £7.50 supplement for trip days
          p
            em Early Bird bookings made up to two weeks before the holidays receive a discount of 10%.
          p
            em Children must be picked up from Sparks by 17:45 at the very latest to avoid a fee.

        section
          h2 How to book and pay
          p If you would like to join Sparks, you’ll first need to register and pay an annual registration fee of £20 per child.
          p The easiest way to register, pay and book is by setting up a #[a(href='https://libacura.co.uk/fd/login/') Libacura account] - a bespoke administration system for after school clubs, which is safe, reliable and straightforward. Have a look at our #[a(href=pageUrl('about/registration-booking.pug#registration')) registration and booking page] to find out more about Libacura.
          p Alternatively, we’re happy to take payment via bank transfer and bookings via email by clicking the link below.
          a.content__cta(href='mailto:coopsparks@gmail.com?subject=Holiday Club booking') Make a booking

        section
          h2 Register with us
          p Booking opens for the Summer Holiday Club on the 13th of June 2017.
          a.content__button(href=pageUrl('about/registration-booking.pug#registration')) Register now
